author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: Franklin: Weak cold front is on the way
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - High clouds yesterday kept temps a little cooler, but still above normal...86°.
We could see about the same today as the upper flow from the west southwest has kept the high cloudiness around this morning and likely through the day.
A weak cold front is on the way for tonight. Plenty of sunshine this weekend with highs a little cooler Saturday; more so on Sunday.
Dew points will also fall allowing morning temps to drop into the 50s and low 60s.
A pretty #sunrise over #nola this morning. Some areas of fog and high clouds to begin this Friday. Milder weekend. pic.twitter.com/OBsssQ11CU
— Chris Franklin (@CFranklinFOX8) October 9, 2015 Follow me on Twitter: @CFranklinFOX8
